## What to extract

**Property groups** are high-level categories of verified properties. They typically have:
- A title (e.g. "Solvency Properties", "Access Control", "Reward Calculation Integrity")
- A description of what the group covers
- An overall verification status
- Optional assumptions or preconditions
- One or more individual rules or invariants

**Rules** are individual CVL rules or invariants within a property group. They have:
- A name (the CVL rule/invariant name, e.g. `integrityOfDeposit`, `totalSupplyIsSumOfBalances`)
- A verification status (e.g. "Verified", "Violated", "Timeout")
- A description of what the rule checks
- A cloud run URL, if one can be matched (see below)

## Guidelines

1. Preserve the report's own grouping structure. If the report organizes properties into numbered sections, use those as property groups.
2. Use the **exact** rule names as they appear in the report â€” these will be used to search for rules in source code. Do not rename, paraphrase, or normalize rule names.
3. For the property group ID, use the section number or a short identifier from the report (e.g. "1", "2a", "solvency").
4. Include ALL rules mentioned, even those with non-verified status (Violated, Timeout, etc.).
5. If assumptions are stated for a group (e.g. "assuming no reentrancy"), capture them verbatim.

